Such a property would make it easier to make archiving decisions.

The existence of this feature would mean that a plugin such as [Archiving Plugin for Confluence|http://midori.hu/products/confluence-archiving-plugin/] wouldn't have to implement it's own [view tracking mechanism|http://midori.hu/products/confluence-archiving-plugin/documentation/view-tracking]. The Atlassian team must be in a better position to implement this optimally in the Confluence core.

h3. Workaround
The AO_92296B_AORECENTLY_VIEWED table will show the LAST_VIEW_DATE:
{code:sql}SELECT * from "AO_92296B_AORECENTLY_VIEWED";{code}

Our corporate branding requires us to insert a strip of content (mainly a logo) above Confluence's menu bar.

If you do this, "Create page" in Internet Explorer (IE8 or IE10) positions the strip at the bottom of the window containing Preview|Save|Cancel buttons off screen.

You must resize the window (or minimise/maximise it if it is full screen) to see the buttons.

This does not happen with Firefox and Chrome, and did not happen in Confluence 4.3.6

To reproduce: add the following to the HEAD section of Custom HTML:

{code:xml}
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.toInit(function () {
   var topOfPage = AJS.$("<div style='height:55px'>text above menu bar</div>");
   AJS.$("div#header-precursor div.cell:first").prepend(topOfPage);
});
</script>
{code}

